 "description": "Semi-intelligent at worst, so always armed: half a band carries clubs (as morning stars), a quarter lance-like spears, the rest composite bows. In melee a Centaur strikes twice — once as a man, once as a medium horse. They den in hidden glens with their females (twice the males' number, unarmed), their young (equal to the males, non-combatant save in extremity), 1-6 additional males, and their treasure.",
